data.title: Pierce Brosnan, 65, and Keely Shaye Smith, 54, look in love after 17 years of marriage at Chanel
data.meta_description: Pierce Brosnan, 65, and Keely Shaye Smith, 54, are still every inch in love after 17 years of wedded bliss. The power couple looked very smitten as they attended a Chanel event in Malibu.
data.text:
Pierce Brosnan, 65, and Keely Shaye Smith, 54, are still every inch in love after 17 years of wedded bliss.

The power couple looked very smitten as they attended a Chanel event in Malibu on Saturday evening.

The former 007 actor and the TV producer were inseparable as they mingled with the A-list crowd.

Keely wore a black dress that was low-cut in front and came below the knee. There was a sheer overlay that added intrigue.

The former TV host added a stunning butterfly necklace and strappy black heels.

And the siren wore her long, black hair down past her shoulders.

Brosnan - whose next film is Mamma Mia! Here We Go Again - was dapper in a light grey suit with brown suede shoes and sunglasses on.

Also at the event was Kathryn Boyd, who looked far from with child as she modeled a stunning white goddess gown.

The blonde fashion designer was with her husband Josh Brolin of Deadpool 2 and Avengers: Infinity War fame.

Also there was his mother-in-law Barbra Streisand.

In late May, the 30-year-old beauty, who used to be the actor's assistant, shared a photo of her belly on Instagram with the caption, 'Something’s cookin... Baby Girl Brolin on the way.'

Josh also took to Instagram to share the good news along with two photos of his lady's bump.

'There’s a new sheriff in town, and she’s no bigger than a sweet potato. Hang on to your hats. #jbkbstucktogether #lilbeanterritory #loveisaslovedoes,' he wrote.

The looker had on a white tank top and grey-and-white sweatpants as they seemed to be on a hike.

Josh already has daughter Eden Brolin, 24, as well as son Trevor Brolin, 29, with ex-wife Alice Adair, who has acted in the films Beverly Hills Cop II and Desperado: Avalanche At Devil's Ridge.

He was also been married to A-list movie star Diane Lane, 53, of Cotton Club and Under The Tuscan Sun fame, but they had no kids.

Because Josh's father James Brolin is married to Streisand, 76, this means the legendary singer will become a step grandmother again.

Julia Roberts still looks like America's Sweetheart. The 50-year-old Pretty Woman actress stood out in a lovely blue outfit at the Chanel party.

This sighting comes after Deadline reported the mother-of-three will present longtime pal and Ocean's 11 co-star George Clooney with an AFI Award.

Roberts lookedblonder than usual and wore a pair of prescription glasses.

And the Runaway Bride star also flashed that megawatt smile that helped make her a box office queen.

Her next project is the movie Ben Is Back.

As far as giving Clooney an award, the AFI event will take place on June 7 at the Dolby Theatre in Hollywood.

Clooney was selected in October as the recipient of the 46th annual AFI Life Achievement Award, with the two-time Oscar winner one of only two people (along with Walt Disney) to be nominated for Academy Awards in six different categories.

The ceremony will air on TNT on June 21 and in September on TCM during a night of programming dedicated to Clooney’s films.

Also at the Chanel event were Jennifer Aniston and Courteney Cox.

Their outing came amid new reports Courteney has chosen Jennifer to be her maid of honor when she weds Snow Patrol's Johnny McDaid.

A source told the Mirror: 'Courteney wouldn’t want to walk down the aisle without Jennifer by her side. They have a very strong friendship.'

Courteney was maid of honor herself when Jennifer tied the knot with her ex Justin Theroux in 2015.

Jen, 49, looked stylish as ever for the event, which held in aid of the Natural Resources Defense Council.

The star opted for a simple black scoop neck tee, which she tucked into some black, sophisticated high-waist trousers.

She bundled up in a matching black blazer with numerous buttons, and added a few inches to her 5ft5in frame with some classic black stilettos heels.

Her famous caramel tresses were parted in the middle, and she appeared to glow thanks to some strategic blush and pale rose lipstick.

Former co-star Courteney, 53, chose a similar ensemble for the upscale event.

The Cougar Town actress paired a white satiny shirt with her own pair of wide leg trousers and black stilettos.

She also decided to part her raven locks down the center, and chose similar shades of blush and lipstick.

There were a plethora of other A-listers in attendance as well, including the forever youthful Cindy Crawford, 52.

The globally-known supermodel wowed as usual in an all white shirt and trouser combo.

Tan heels and a large gold chain necklace rounded out her simple but pleasing outfit.

Cindy's husband Rande Gerber and her son Presley were also on hand to escort her to the festivities.

Sports Illustrated vet Molly Sims, 45, delighted in a sunflower yellow frock decorated with light pink flowers.

She secured it with an elaborately-tied black belt.

Baywatch star Priyanka Chopra, 35, turned heads thanks to her heather grey knit jumpsuit with flared legs.

Leslie Mann, 46, of Knocked Up fame looked to be having a ball in her multicolored top, which she tucked into a pair of wide leg dark-wash jeans.

90210 star Sara Foster, 37, went with an eye-catching rose-colored dress emblazoned with shiny floral embellishments.

The multi-talented Mandy Moore, 34, donned a relatively demure black ensemble.
